President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Scott Doney, a senior scientist at the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution, is nominated for the position of Chief Scientist at the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration. Nancy E. Lindborg, the President of Mercy Corps, is nominated for Assistant Administrator of the Democracy, Conflict, and Humanitarian Assistance Bureau at USAID. Kevin Nealer, a Principal and Partner at The Scowcroft Group, is nominated for a position on the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. Chase T. Rogers, the Chief Justice of the Connecticut Supreme Court, is nominated for a position on the State Justice Institute. Wilfredo Martinez, a County Court Judge in Florida, is also nominated for a position on the State Justice Institute. Lastly, Warren Michael Stern, a Senior Advisor at the Office of the Assistant Secretary of State for International Security and Nonproliferation, is appointed as Director of the Domestic Nuclear Detection Office at the Department of Homeland Security.